description:
In my local Virtuoso, given a graph http://localhost:8890/DAV/onlyOneTriple — for a simplest example, with only one triple and one assertion of namespace, there is the content:
@prefix wikidata:	<http://www.wikidata.org/entity/> .
<https://cantusdatabase.org/chant/467250> wikidata:P136 wikidata:Q582093 .
Then, my query codes in ISQL are:
SPARQL
DEFINE input:grab-all "yes"
DEFINE input:grab-depth 2
DEFINE input:grab-limit 200

SELECT *
FROM NAMED <http://localhost:8890/DAV/onlyOneTriple>
WHERE {
  GRAPH ?g {
    ?s ?p ?o .
    FILTER(STRSTARTS(STR(?o), "http://www.wikidata.org/entity/")) # Ensure the object is a Wikidata entity
  }
  SERVICE <https://query.wikidata.org/sparql> {
    ?o ?wikidataProperty ?wikidataValue .
  }
};

— These codes are modified with the help of GPT4 in order to grab related data from Wikidata.
Hereby, while according to the significance of sponge I understood, it can grab the external data, for example, from Wikidata; as long as there are Wikidata resources which have the same URI with the entities from http://localhost:8890/DAV/Jun (as shown in the example codes above), there must be data retrieved upon execution. However, as I executed as above, there was no data feeding back. Is there something wrong, or could somebody please illustrate with some other example codes which generates outcome?
